Barry Turner lives alone in a fifth-floor walkup on a quiet street in the Prospect Heights section of Brooklyn.
He's a nervous man.
Fidgets all the time.
He smokes Kool cigarettes and drinks prodigious amounts of orange Kool-Aid.
He suffers from obsessive-compulsive disorder.
He takes two types of medication to stave off psychotic episodes.
When I would ride the subways, yeah, my mouth would start twitching.
